latestIgtvVideos.title: coolasianmum’s guide-to-life
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
A @cityofsydney supported project birthed from having to move home and live with my Mum due to the impacts of the virus. 

Cool Asian Mum's Guide to Life is a compilation of life lessons and old Chinese Wives' Tales that my mum can't help but pass onto me.

Shout out @fezshaheen and @hungryjaack for being my guinea pigs. 

And of course, mad appreciation for the star herself, @coolasianmum. Thanks for the life lessons that raised me into the person I am today 💕💕💕

latestIgtvVideos.title: HOME FEED
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Our response “to create something in your home” for @_homefeed, a virtual showcase created by @catsantos, @zoeemoves and @caetlynwatson. A Fkn sick way to escape our current situations and enjoy dance...just cuz. 
Thanks for having us legends. Keen for more!

Dancing with my fav @hungryjaack 
Music by our fav @mohibeats. Make sure you check the YouTube channel for more vids from the dance community. 💕💕💕

latestIgtvVideos.title: 婆婆’s house
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Cuts from one long ass set I did on the rooftop of my grandma’s house in Guangzhou. Tbh I felt pretty underwhelmed by myself watching this back. (Probs the month’s worth of bubble teas I’ve consumed)

I definitely wasn’t keen to post this but then I read this “inspo post” about how no one can tell you if you’re freestyling wrong or right coz it’s just you expressing yourself and figured why the fuck not (2020 energy and all that). Hopefully someone else feels this and also shares something they were feeling eh about. I mean it’s just the internet, right? 🤷🏻‍♀️

latestIgtvVideos.title: Sooo, what do you do?
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
I find it really hard to explain to people what I do. So, here’s what I wish I could say when people ask. :) Direction + edit + Music: me

WACKIE JU 002 Saviour @ausfashionweek 

Movement Directing for this show was truly a planets coming into alignment type of feeling. 🪐✨

The collection “Honours the resilience of the Chinese cultural legacy, commemorating the history of blood shed on the sacred land; extending that respect to similar experiences in contemporary society.”- JW

Endless love to @wackie.ju for trusting me with your world. It was an honour and a privilege.

Thankyou 1000x to @alicerobinson_ my movement assist + the other half of my brain. I could not have executed this without you. 🤍🪽

a 5-hour heels intensive dedicated to moving with clarity, confidence & essence.

[ limited spots ]
BOOK VIA LINK IN BIO

Pilates for Dancers
Heels Technique
Heels Choreography
Q&A

WEEKEND ONE — INTERMEDIATE: Bridging the Gap
For dancers who are comfortable in beg heels but want to refine their technique, musicality and performance quality. We’ll break things down + build back up - bridging the gap between “doing steps” and truly embodying the movement.

Focus:
Understanding body placement in heels
Building strength, control and balance
Practising textures, walks, and weight shifts
Pushing towards cleaner execution and essence

WEEKEND TWO — ADVANCED: Find Your Essence
This day is for experienced heels dancers or adv dancers looking to develop their artistry through performance, musicality, and essence in a heel.

Focus:
Transferring your existing movement quality to a heel Executing with texture, clarity and essence
Mindset, performance & retention
Working smarter not harder with your body
